00:05:49.080 --> 00:05:53.810
Carrots and sticks are powerful motivators.
But that second drive -- to respond to rewards

00:05:53.810 --> 00:05:57.710
and punishments in our environment -- is obviously
part of what it is to be human.

00:05:57.710 --> 00:06:02.159
But, it's not All that it is to be human.
No one would ever say that's all we are.

00:06:02.159 --> 00:06:06.569
We have other drives too, right?
We have the John drive -- the biological drive.

00:06:06.569 --> 00:06:08.550
We have the Martin drive -- the reward and
punishment drive.

00:06:08.550 --> 00:06:13.259
But we also have a third drive.
We do things because they're interesting.

00:06:13.259 --> 00:06:17.719
We do things because we like to do them.
We do things because we're curious, because

00:06:17.719 --> 00:06:20.219
we want to learn, because we want to make
a contribution.

00:06:20.219 --> 00:06:24.069
That is also part of what it is to be human
 -- that third drive to do things for their

00:06:24.069 --> 00:06:28.550
own sake, because they're interesting, because
we get better at them, because they advance

00:06:28.550 --> 00:06:32.389
some kind of purpose.
Now, does that make sense? We have those drives.

00:06:32.389 --> 00:06:35.520
And for those of you who -- actually, there
were a handful of you who looked a little

00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:40.289
