 -- that was kind of a rhetorical question.

00:15:31.892 --> 00:15:38.850
[laughter]
After the introduction of the fine, we observed

00:15:38.850 --> 00:15:45.100
a steady "increase" in the number of parents
coming late.

00:15:45.100 --> 00:15:51.190
The rate was finally settled at a level that
was higher and almost twice as large as the

00:15:51.190 --> 00:15:57.190
initial one.
So you impose a fine to deter bad behavior

00:15:57.190 --> 00:16:02.000
and the consequence of the fine is, you get
"more" of the bad behavior?

00:16:02.000 --> 00:16:05.240
And then what happened?
You double the rate of bad behavior, and then,

00:16:05.240 --> 00:16:08.490
when you withdraw -- I don't have this in
