00:16:30.690 --> 00:16:39.480
So people who couldn't make it there on time
thought, "Oh no big deal I'll just pay this

00:16:39.480 --> 00:16:41.920
money and show up late".

00:16:41.920 --> 00:16:45.350
Daniel Pink: You said, "It's no big deal to
show up late, I'll just pay them money."

00:16:45.350 --> 00:16:49.810
Why were people showing up late -- why were
most people showing up on time in the first

00:16:49.810 --> 00:16:51.070
place under the earlier regime?

00:16:51.070 --> 00:16:54.580
Patsy: They didn't think they had an option
probably.

00:16:54.580 --> 00:16:55.580
Daniel Pink: They didn't think they had an
option?

00:16:55.580 --> 00:16:59.200
What is another reason you think they might
have been showing up on time?

00:16:59.200 --> 00:17:12.299
Social convention? Okay. What else?
Guilty? Shame? They liked their kids? [audience

00:17:12.299 --> 00:17:18.929
laughter]
They didn't want their child to sit on the

00:17:18.929 --> 00:17:25.089
street.
Here's the thing -- okay, this is good.

00:17:25.089 --> 00:17:29.289
Their relationship with the caregiver was
